{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"350a84f4-dd5f-414c-86cf-948612f07cf1","content":"The project doesn't exist yet at that path, but here's how to configure `.vscode/mcp.json` for a C# MCP server using **stdio** transport:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Place this file at `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root.\n- `type: \"stdio\"` means Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- Your C# server must read JSON-RPC requests from stdin and write responses to stdout (e.g., using the `ModelContextProtocol` NuGet package with `UseStdioServerTransport()`).\n- Make sure your server does **not** write logs or debug output to stdout — use stderr instead.\n\nIf you're using **SSE/HTTP** transport instead, replace with:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"sse\",\n      \"url\": \"http://localhost:5000/sse\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"25daa656-a07a-4d1d-884f-c3b8018a6c95","outputTokens":315,"requestId":"1584:301230:316BF4B:361CF69:69FBE5D4"},"id":"d40a7fb6-f620-4173-b448-cf6cded1ac21","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:07:40.316Z","parentId":"946847b4-42b2-4023-b038-4d5c44b6ec13"}
